<p>Better than that, you can fold them up in your suitcase and they don‚Äôt wrinkle (or if they do, you can iron them!). Plus, they have the same DPI as paper, they‚Äôre cheaper, and you can easily re-use them (either as a poster or as a superhero cape). Still not sold? Check out these photos from IEEE Vis in Paris. The conference organizers needed to take down the posters quickly, and almost anyone with a paper poster ended up with something ripped, wrinkled, and taped to someone else‚Äôs poster.</p>

