<p>Okay, so how do you do it? <a href="http://ascb.org/how-to-print-a-fabric-poster/">This post</a> is fantastic, and it‚Äôs where I learned how to print a fabric poster. For whatever reason, that link keeps changing, so I‚Äôll summarize the main points:</p>

<ul>
  <li>use the website <a href="http://www.spoonflower.com">spoonflower.com</a></li>
  <li>choose the ‚Äúperformance knit‚Äù fabric, which should cost around $25</li>
  <li>upload your poster <strong>as a png</strong> (ignore at your peril!)</li>
  <li>make sure it looks right, and order!</li>
</ul>

<p>Printing and shipping is variable, but Spoonflower has a data-driven page that will tell you <a href="http://help.spoonflower.com/customer/portal/articles/1173283-how-long-will-it-take-to-get-my-order-">how many days production is currently taking</a>. If you need your poster quickly, you can pay for rush shipping, but either way the poster will come folded up in one of those soft plastic envelopes that fits easily into any mailbox. What are you waiting for?</p>
